body_html: The dependency only makes sense for Python 2 as concurrent.futures has been added to Python 3's standard library (see https://docs.python.org/3/library/concurrent.futures.html and https://www.python.org/dev/peps/pep-3148/).

body: The dependency only makes sense for Python 2 as `concurrent.futures` has been added to Python 3's standard library (see https://docs.python.org/3/library/concurrent.futures.html and https://www.python.org/dev/peps/pep-3148/).
